\pard\f0\fs28 Creeping perennial herb rooting at the nodes. Leaves petiolate, simple, entire. Flowers axillary, solitary. Corolla divided to about halfway into 5 erect lobes. Stamens inserted near the top of the corolla-tube, more or less included. Ovary 2-locular; styles 2; stigmas capitate. Capsule 2-lobed; lobes usually 1-seeded.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Literature: A. Lawalree, {\i Acta Bot. Neerl.}{\b  19}: 717-721 (1970).
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. D. micrantha} Urban, {\i Symb. Antill.}{\b  9}: 243 (1924) ({\i D. repens} auct. eur., non J. R. & G. Forster). Stems up to 50 cm, pubescent, slender. Lamina of leaf 5-30 × 5-30 mm, orbicular to reniform, appressed-pubescent; petiole 5-50 mm. Peduncle 3-20 mm; calyx 1·5-2·5 mm, sericeous, divided to more than halfway; corolla 2-2·5 mm, whitish or greenish.{\i  Naturalized in grassland and open sandy ground in W. Europe.} [Az Br It.] ({\i E. Asia}.)
